<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB07853</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT MANDATING EVERY PASSENGER VESSEL OR SHIP TO SET UP ON BOARD WELL-EQUIPPED MEDICAL CLINIC MANNED BY COMPETENT MEDICAL STAFF AND PRESCRIBING PENALTIES FOR VIOLATIONS THEREOF AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Mandates all passenger vessels or ships to set up on board a medical clinic equipped with basic life saving devices, to be manned by competent medical staff to look after the health and well-being of their passengers, especially during medical emergencies.
</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ALIAS NAME : “Medical Clinic on Ship Act”</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>CASTELO, WINSTON &quot;WINNIE&quot;</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2018-06-06</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Tambunting (000 2018-08-14)</td><td>2. Sangcopan (000 2018-09-19)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON TRANSPORTATION ON 2018-07-30</td></tr></table>